00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:38,230
The one who throws money around?

280
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:39,110
It's him.

281
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:40,140
Seems like him.

282
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:44,110
Support the Divine Mountains and Seas.

283
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:45,780
Welcome.

284
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:47,860
- Hello. Welcome.
- Hello. Welcome.

285
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,070
♪Baby, I'm a monster♪

286
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:54,710
Welcome.

287
00:10:54,710 --> 00:10:55,620
Please come in.

288
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:58,020
♪Blow up♪

289
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,660
♪Baby, I'm a monster♪

290
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,260
♪Rock the way♪

291
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:05,070
♪Rock the way♪

292
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:07,740
(Support #TheDivineMountainsandSeas#)

293
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:09,249
(Game Download Rankings)

294
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,660
(Infinite Imagination,
The Divine Mountains and Seas)

295
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:13,620
(Powerful Launch,
Pre-Registration Welcomed)

296
00:11:14,413 --> 00:11:16,540
(Crafted By Skilled Masters
to Build A Beautiful World)

297
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:18,180
(The Divine Mountains and Seas.
Explore the Unknown.)

298
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:21,540
Sorry.

299
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:25,420
(The Divine Mountains and Seas.
Explore the Unknown. Fearless Heroes.)

300
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,110
Everyone.

301
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:28,660
Keep eating

302
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:29,740
and don't stop looking.

303
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:30,780
Here, look this way.

304
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,710
The Divine Mountains and Seas.

305
00:11:32,710 --> 00:11:34,380
Tengda's newest game.

306
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:35,350
It's super fun.

307
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:37,020
Well... There's a QR code.

308
00:11:37,020 --> 00:11:38,470
Everyone can scan it to register.

309
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:39,780
Anyone who registers by scanning

310
00:11:39,780 --> 00:11:40,620
gets free dishes.

311
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:41,230
Okay?

312
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:42,780
Scan it.

313
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:43,990
Scan here.

314
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:47,620
Mr. Li Jr.,

315
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:49,110
why are you doing this yourself?

316
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:50,310
Quick, I'll do it.

317
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:51,724
Look, how many times have I told you?

318
00:11:51,724 --> 00:11:53,835
You need to spread them out.
Why put them all together?

319
00:11:53,835 --> 00:11:55,070
Is this resource integration?

320
00:11:55,070 --> 00:11:55,500
Right?

321
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,020
Your info needs to be direct.

322
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:58,590
You just need to...

323
00:11:59,350 --> 00:11:59,590
Here.

324
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:00,500
Move aside.

325
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:01,950
Mr. Li Jr.,

326
00:12:02,190 --> 00:12:03,140
it's Mr. Li calling.

327
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:04,780
Tell him I'm busy.

328
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:05,620
I'll call back later.

329
00:12:06,990 --> 00:12:07,590
Mr. Li.

330
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:08,350
Mr. Li Jr. is...

331
00:12:09,590 --> 00:12:10,500
Yes.

332
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:11,860
Mr. Li Jr.,

333
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:13,710
Mr. Li sounds angry.

334
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:18,710
This one.

335
00:12:22,310 --> 00:12:22,780
Dad.

336
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:24,780
This time, Tengda is up against

337
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:27,070
Fingle under the Dayake Group.

338
00:12:27,470 --> 00:12:29,260
Why can Fingle secure so many

339
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,350
overseas game licenses?

340
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:33,500
It's because it's backed by Dayake.

341
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,470
You know

342
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:36,540
the interests involved.

343
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:38,620
You openly supporting Tengda like this

344
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:40,350
will cause unimaginable trouble

345
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:42,020
for Fuhui.

346
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,020
No, Dad, I really...

347
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:47,430
I barely recognize you now.

348
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:49,540
You never cared about this before.

349
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,950
Yes, Fuhui has grown strong lately,

350
00:12:51,991 --> 00:12:52,900
but what about you?

351
00:12:52,924 --> 00:12:54,500
You care
more and more about connections

352
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,900
and appearances.

353
00:12:56,260 --> 00:12:57,260
Do these things

354
00:12:57,260 --> 00:12:58,620
matter more than your son?

355
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,780
Times have changed.

356
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:02,230
Fuhui today

357
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:04,470
has countless eyes watching it.

358
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:05,470
Shi.

359
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:07,380
You're not a child anymore.

360
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:09,780
It's not the time to care about loyalty.

361
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:11,860
Sacrificing the small to save the big

362
00:13:12,368 --> 00:13:14,110
is something you don't need me to teach.

363
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:15,950
Got it, Dad.

364
00:13:16,857 --> 00:13:18,260
Fingle is wealthy and powerful.

365
00:13:18,620 --> 00:13:20,430
Once the game launched,
it crushed Tengda.

366
00:13:20,540 --> 00:13:22,230
Isn't it because Tengda is new

367
00:13:22,230 --> 00:13:23,500
and took some of your market?

368
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:25,500
But, Dad,

369
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:28,070
I think what we should consider now

370
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:29,660
isn't how to monopolize.

371
00:13:29,660 --> 00:13:30,740
What we should think about

372
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,500
is how to make it bigger.

373
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,350
Isn't that right?

374
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:35,620
If an industry

375
00:13:35,620 --> 00:13:37,140
has only one player,

376
00:13:37,620 --> 00:13:38,430
that industry

377
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:40,070
is truly finished.

378
00:14:05,657 --> 00:14:07,470
(Game Category Rankings)
They used Tengda's businesses

379
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:09,170
to promote
the Divine Mountains and Seas.

380
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,500
Download stats and online popularity

381
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:12,230
are rebounding.

382
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:14,140
We need to think of another way.

383
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:16,470
I can't lose this time.

384
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,230
This is our last chance.

385
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:23,230
I didn't expect Tengda
to be this resilient.

386
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:24,780
I thought

387
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:25,860
we'd beat them

388
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:27,310
with no chance to recover.

389
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:29,470
Looks like...

390
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,110
We'll have to go all out.

391
00:14:40,457 --> 00:14:41,413
(Stay true to our mission,
succeed for the greater good.)

392
00:14:41,413 --> 00:14:42,830
(Through a video leaked from Tengda,)

393
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:43,830
(we can see)

394
00:14:43,830 --> 00:14:46,950
(Tengda's English name is Tengda,)

395
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:49,830
(but it's written as Tenda on the wall.)

396
00:14:49,830 --> 00:14:50,740
(One G is missing.)

397
00:14:50,740 --> 00:14:52,110
(They can't even spell)

398
00:14:52,110 --> 00:14:53,350
(their own name correctly.)

399
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:55,070
(You can see that it's full of bugs.)

400
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:57,740
(And Tengda's abbreviation is TD.)
[*"TD" can stand for "unsubscribe" in Chinese. ]

401
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:59,310
(It obviously means unsubscribe.)

402
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:02,260
How childish.

403
00:15:02,613 --> 00:15:04,213
There's something even more childish.

404
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:05,470
Look.

405
00:15:05,546 --> 00:15:07,710
(Expert Who Can't Soar)
The new set by Infinite Imagination

406
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:09,590
is called Expert Who Can't Soar.

407
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:11,110
This is too much.

408
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:12,590
Let's make one, too.

409
00:15:12,590 --> 00:15:13,350
Make

410
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:15,020
a dull, lifeless rock.

411
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:16,350
They attack Tengda,

412
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:17,470
and you scold their leader.

413
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:18,740
Wouldn't that make it easier

414
00:15:18,740 --> 00:15:19,900
for them to find faults?

415
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:24,110
Then what should we do?

416
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:26,990
It seems
Fingle hasn't done anything wrong.

417
00:15:26,990 --> 00:15:28,360
They made a game for the first time

418
00:15:28,368 --> 00:15:29,670
and were led astray by Zhou Muyan.

419
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:31,260
Didn't Mr. Pei say

420
00:15:31,470 --> 00:15:32,590
those attacking us

421
00:15:32,590 --> 00:15:33,590
are just minor nuisances?

422
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:35,070
Just ignore them.

423
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:40,900
Wait.

424
00:15:41,470 --> 00:15:42,230
Now

425
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:43,350
it's no longer minor.

426
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:44,230
Look.

427
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:46,860
I searched
the Divine Mountains and Seas online.

428
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,435
All results are Infinite Imagination.

429
00:15:48,591 --> 00:15:49,590
What does this mean?

430
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:53,020
Did they block our keywords?

431
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:00,020
They actually did.

432
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:01,880
Anything
about the Divine Mountains and Seas

433
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:03,140
shows Infinite Imagination.

434
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:05,230
This tactic is too shady.

435
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:07,140
Check Net blocked us.

436
00:16:07,140 --> 00:16:07,950
Check Net

437
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:09,500
dominates all search engines.

438
00:16:09,546 --> 00:16:11,560
If everyone searches
the Divine Mountains and Seas,

439
00:16:11,568 --> 00:16:12,768
it automatically redirects

440
00:16:12,768 --> 00:16:14,110
to Infinite Imagination's results.

441
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:16,660
That'll cause us big trouble.

442
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,500
Zhou Muyan clearly did this.

443
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,110
Our data just started to rise,

444
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:22,457
and he played dirty tricks again.

445
00:16:22,502 --> 00:16:23,590
Though not clever,

446
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:25,070
it's effective.

447
00:16:25,830 --> 00:16:27,350
They probably aren't just messing

448
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:28,368
with the search engines.

449
00:16:28,435 --> 00:16:29,260
I'll check elsewhere.

450
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,780
We're likely

451
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:36,020
blocked on other websites too.

452
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:41,990
Everyone.

453
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,620
Something happened again.

454
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:46,180
(Conference Room)

455
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:48,350
Now it's not just Check Net.

456
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,110
Almost on all social platforms

457
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:52,230
and short video platforms,
our traffic can't rise.

458
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:53,350
I asked Mr. Qiao.

459
00:16:53,350 --> 00:16:54,380
He said this is called

460
00:16:54,380 --> 00:16:56,435
traffic limiting,
keyword blocking, or something.

461
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,140
Our keywords have been blocked.

462
00:16:58,900 --> 00:16:59,924
Mainly, we haven't had

463
00:16:59,924 --> 00:17:02,350
any binding cooperation
with other platforms.

464
00:17:02,350 --> 00:17:03,302
We're indeed passive now.

465
00:17:03,302 --> 00:17:05,280
Once everyone searches
the Divine Mountains and Seas,

466
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,130
it automatically links
to Infinite Imagination.

467
00:17:07,580 --> 00:17:09,100
Why does Zhou Muyan

468
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:10,470
have so many despicable tricks?

469
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,710
How much did he pay these companies?

470
00:17:12,910 --> 00:17:14,230
We pay double, triple,

471
00:17:14,230 --> 00:17:15,710
and make them block them online!

472
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:17,230
If we do this,

473
00:17:17,235 --> 00:17:18,540
how are we different from him?

474
00:17:19,470 --> 00:17:20,950
It's different.

475
00:17:21,213 --> 00:17:23,780
Mr. Pei, the Divine Mountains and Seas
is the fruit of our labor.

476
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:25,060
We must win this time.

477
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:30,020
Sibo.

478
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,300
Look at you.

479
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,430
Working 9-to-6 every day,

480
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:33,780
your eye bags are huge.

481
00:17:33,780 --> 00:17:35,740
Is it different from overtime
at the old company?

482
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:37,430
Everyday, Infinite Imagination

483
00:17:37,430 --> 00:17:39,100
updates, gives benefits,

484
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,990
and updates for big gift packs.

485
00:17:40,990 --> 00:17:41,990
My upgrade resource pack

486
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:42,910
must keep up,

487
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:44,430
or users won't stay.

488
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:45,230
Lv.

489
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,060
How long has it been
since you left on time?

490
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,780
Aren't you supposed to be a slasher?

491
00:17:48,780 --> 00:17:50,950
No time for that now.

492
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:53,020
Zhou Muyan is full of dirty tricks.

493
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,740
And you.

494
00:17:54,857 --> 00:17:56,020
I don't even want to say it.

495
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:57,740
You lose your temper thrice a day now.

496
00:17:57,740 --> 00:17:59,060
What? Ate gunpowder?

497
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:01,540
I'm not losing my temper, Mr. Pei.

498
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,910
Look online.

499
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:04,340
It's full of bad reviews.

500
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,100
Look.

501
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:07,060
(Does Tengda think they're all that)

502
00:18:07,060 --> 00:18:08,190
(because some of their games succeed?)

503
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:09,670
(They think their products
are guaranteed hits?)

504
00:18:09,670 --> 00:18:10,950
(When it comes to big games, we can see)

505
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:12,430
(the real production level
of some companies.)

506
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:14,230
(I suggest playing Infinite Imagination.)

507
00:18:14,340 --> 00:18:15,020
Mr. Pei.

508
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:16,820
I understand your point.

509
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,630
Of course, we can't

510
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:19,260
be like Zhou Muyan and his kind.

511
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:22,230
But if we don't act, what about
the Divine Mountains and Seas?

512
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:23,670
Do we just watch them

513
00:18:23,670 --> 00:18:25,260
suppress us?

514
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:26,540
Yeah.

515
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:27,540
Look.

516
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:33,150
I know.

517
00:18:33,430 --> 00:18:35,740
Everyone gave their all
to the Divine Mountains and Seas.

518
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,430
It's indeed a good game.

519
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:39,020
Everyone has high expectations for it.

520
00:18:39,230 --> 00:18:41,020
So, getting this feedback after launch,

521
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:41,780
everyone is angry.

522
00:18:41,780 --> 00:18:42,670
Me too.

523
00:18:43,150 --> 00:18:44,300
But are these comments

524
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,630
only from

525
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:46,990
Zhou Muyan's slander?

526
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:49,060
Mr. Pei,

527
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,630
if you put it that way,

528
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:51,820
you reminded me.

529
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:53,740
When I was at Sky Fire,

530
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:55,060
I already felt it.

531
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:56,060
Think about it.

532
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:57,300
Tengda,

533
00:18:57,540 --> 00:18:58,780
a new company,

534
00:18:58,780 --> 00:19:01,020
made four games that all succeeded.

535
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:02,950
Competitors are watching.

536
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:04,190
The Divine Mountains and Seas

537
00:19:04,190 --> 00:19:05,580
is our first

538
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:07,260
large-scale multiplayer online game.

539
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:09,910
Many veteran game companies

540
00:19:09,910 --> 00:19:11,260
already disliked us.

541
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:13,146
So they waited for Zhou Muyan
to spread rumors,

542
00:19:13,146 --> 00:19:14,500
and everyone piled on.

543
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:17,150
Lin Wan.

544
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:19,430
Do you remember I asked you

545
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:21,020
why you like making games?

546
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:25,340
Reality is sometimes too heavy.

547
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:27,500
We want a safe harbor

548
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:29,020
and a utopia.

549
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:33,060
Yes.

550
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:35,230
Life

551
00:19:35,230 --> 00:19:37,300
can suffocate people.

552
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:39,990
You can't escape it,

553
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:42,500
but we can nap

554
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:43,580
and dream.

555
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,500
You have ideals

556
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:46,710
and emotions.

557
00:19:46,910 --> 00:19:48,230
I believe you can do it.

558
00:19:52,430 --> 00:19:53,950
Because games

559
00:19:53,950 --> 00:19:55,780
can let many people

560
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:58,820
momentarily forget the harsh reality.

561
00:20:00,710 --> 00:20:01,540
Now,

562
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:04,430
can it still make you forget
reality's troubles?

563
00:20:10,580 --> 00:20:11,260
A creation

564
00:20:11,580 --> 00:20:13,230
is actually the creators'

565
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:14,990
true emotional vessel

566
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:16,150
and reflection.

567
00:20:16,470 --> 00:20:17,470
But look.

568
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:20,100
Everyone is full of worries every day,

569
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:21,190
trapped in marketing wars.

570
00:20:21,190 --> 00:20:22,020
Can we

571
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:24,020
still create happiness for players?

572
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:24,950
We now

573
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,260
betray our original intention

574
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:27,740
and drift farther away.

575
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:33,100
If games

576
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:35,150
want to attract players,

577
00:20:35,390 --> 00:20:37,540
they can only rely on heartfelt content

578
00:20:37,540 --> 00:20:38,910
and new gameplay.

579
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:40,820
We should

580
00:20:40,820 --> 00:20:42,430
calm down and think about

581
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:44,470
what we can do
for the Divine Mountains and Seas.

582
00:20:44,470 --> 00:20:46,910
Is it just about defeating
a mere Zhou Muyan?

583
00:20:46,910 --> 00:20:48,190
Zhou Muyan's nothing.

584
00:20:48,190 --> 00:20:49,300
Trash.

585
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,780
He's an industry parasite.

586
00:20:51,470 --> 00:20:53,300
People like Zhou Muyan

587
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:54,500
will never disappear.

588
00:20:54,910 --> 00:20:56,580
If we want a real rival,

589
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:58,500
there's only one.

590
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:00,670
It's ourselves.

591
00:21:14,260 --> 00:21:15,540
I saw a comment saying

592
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:16,910
there are too many newbie tasks.

593
00:21:17,630 --> 00:21:18,870
They're right.

594
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,060
I recently thought about it carefully.

595
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:23,470
We set up
many gameplay features and characters,

596
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:25,430
pushing them all to players at once.

597
00:21:25,820 --> 00:21:27,150
This makes newbie tasks

598
00:21:27,150 --> 00:21:28,300
tedious and long.

599
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:30,870
I take responsibility for this.

600
00:21:30,870 --> 00:21:31,950
When I played earlier,

601
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:33,580
I felt the time in the newbie village

602
00:21:33,580 --> 00:21:34,302
was too long.

603
00:21:34,324 --> 00:21:35,540
I couldn't enter the main map.

604
00:21:35,740 --> 00:21:38,340
Bao, you should have mentioned it
during the test play.

605
00:21:38,340 --> 00:21:39,870
I thought it was a minor issue.

606
00:21:39,870 --> 00:21:41,324
Because once you get to the main map,

607
00:21:41,346 --> 00:21:42,150
it's really fun.

608
00:21:42,150 --> 00:21:43,710
You enlightened me.

609
00:21:44,060 --> 00:21:45,820
I think it's similar
to writing a script.

610
00:21:46,102 --> 00:21:47,710
If the story background is too complex,

611
00:21:47,990 --> 00:21:48,990
the audience abandons it.

612
00:21:48,990 --> 00:21:49,580
Right?

613
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:50,430
- Yes.
- Yes.

614
00:21:50,430 --> 00:21:51,260
Exactly.

615
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:52,580
Then I'll optimize the program.

616
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:53,820
I'll put those gift packs and XP

617
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:55,100
into the tasks.

618
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:56,740
Will this improve the player experience?

619
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:57,710
Definitely.

620
00:21:57,710 --> 00:21:59,470
Another optimization method

621
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:01,430
is to let players

622
00:22:01,430 --> 00:22:02,630
interact with the real world

623
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:04,013
in the Divine Mountains and Seas.

624
00:22:04,013 --> 00:22:04,724
For example,

625
00:22:04,724 --> 00:22:06,100
when players reach a restaurant

626
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,480
in the Divine Mountains and Seas map,

627
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,770
they can actually order takeout

628
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:10,910
and have it delivered to them
in real life.

629
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,500
Good idea.

630
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,230
This really breaks
the dimensional barrier.

631
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:15,390
This can work, right?

632
00:22:15,390 --> 00:22:16,500
No problem.

633
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:16,950
Huang.

634
00:22:16,950 --> 00:22:17,968
Can we have players

635
00:22:17,991 --> 00:22:20,013
read Zhongdian Web Fiction novels
in-game?

636
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:21,260
That should be fine.

637
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:23,150
Don't we

638
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:24,500
have a wishing pool area?

639
00:22:24,630 --> 00:22:25,710
Can players

640
00:22:25,710 --> 00:22:27,150
directly message Mr. Ma's

641
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:29,020
Dreams Fulfilled Immediately account?

642
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:30,150
- Yes.
- Yes!

643
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:32,500
Adding real-world interaction
like this makes it even more fun.

644
00:22:32,502 --> 00:22:33,100
Of course.

645
00:22:33,630 --> 00:22:34,540
I also have an idea.

646
00:22:34,780 --> 00:22:35,910
When I play the game,

647
00:22:35,910 --> 00:22:36,950
there's a character

648
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:37,990
with a really long face

649
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:39,470
and very small eyes.

650
00:22:39,470 --> 00:22:40,630
I think it doesn't look good.

651
00:22:40,635 --> 00:22:41,540
Let's ask our art team

652
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:42,990
to fix it up first.

653
00:22:42,990 --> 00:22:43,500
Can we...

654
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:44,540
Lin Wan, let me tell you.

655
00:22:44,540 --> 00:22:45,470
Well... No.

656
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:46,230
Can we...

657
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:47,060
This way...

658
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:47,470
This...

659
00:22:47,870 --> 00:22:48,500
This...

660
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:51,710
Wait...

661
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:54,020
Isn't being ugly a problem?

662
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:54,910
Being ugly.

663
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:56,740
Shouldn't we reflect on that too?

664
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:04,140
(Stay true to our mission,
succeed for the greater good.)

665
00:23:04,260 --> 00:23:05,260
Ms. Lin Wan.

666
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,368
Thank you for your hard work.

667
00:23:06,391 --> 00:23:07,470
- Ms. Lin Wan.
- Ms. Lin Wan.

668
00:23:07,740 --> 00:23:08,500
Ms. Lin Wan.

669
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:10,013
Thank you for your hard work. Yada.

670
00:23:10,340 --> 00:23:11,230
Comrades.

671
00:23:11,230 --> 00:23:12,100
Infinite Imagination

672
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:14,230
is still increasing player benefits.

673
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:15,150
Listen up.

674
00:23:15,740 --> 00:23:17,230
Hello, players.

675
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:19,546
To thank you for loving and supporting
Infinite Imagination,

676
00:23:19,591 --> 00:23:20,630
starting today,

677
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:22,990
anyone who registers
Infinite Imagination

678
00:23:22,990 --> 00:23:23,820
will receive

679
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:24,740
discounts on downloads

680
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:27,060
for other games published by Fingle.

681
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:29,213
(Infinite Imagination)
Log in and play over two hours

682
00:23:29,213 --> 00:23:30,340
for seven consecutive days,

683
00:23:30,340 --> 00:23:32,260
and you can download other Fingle games

684
00:23:32,260 --> 00:23:34,150
for free.

685
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:36,235
Fingle really went all out.

686
00:23:36,235 --> 00:23:38,500
They spend money to promote
other games they represent,

687
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,440
bleeding funds
to support Infinite Imagination.

688
00:23:40,670 --> 00:23:41,710
Don't worry about them.

689
00:23:42,470 --> 00:23:44,430
Just focus on our own work.

690
00:23:44,710 --> 00:23:46,470
Remember what Mr. Pei said?

691
00:23:46,870 --> 00:23:48,591
- Surpass yourself.
- Surpass yourself.

692
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:50,150
Back to work.

693
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:52,910
Wei.

694
00:23:52,968 --> 00:23:54,500
Have the newbie missions been optimized?

695
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,580
We simplified them.

696
00:23:55,580 --> 00:23:56,910
They're no longer cumbersome.

697
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:58,060
Yeah.

698
00:23:58,060 --> 00:23:59,340
The game's trial experience

699
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:00,300
is much better now.

700
00:24:00,580 --> 00:24:01,500
Lv, Yada.

701
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:02,540
Is it okay on your end?

702
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:04,910
Mr. Pei really reminded me.

703
00:24:04,910 --> 00:24:06,230
I was only writing code,

704
00:24:06,230 --> 00:24:07,870
completely ignoring player feedback.

705
00:24:07,990 --> 00:24:09,670
We need to communicate more with PMs.

706
00:24:10,060 --> 00:24:10,630
Don't worry.

707
00:24:10,630 --> 00:24:12,213
I've put all the rewards and gift packs

708
00:24:12,235 --> 00:24:12,990
into the missions.

709
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:14,430
Fully coordinating with Lv.

710
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:15,710
The update will go live soon.

711
00:24:16,470 --> 00:24:17,300
Mr. Pei is right.

712
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,580
A game attracts players with gameplay.

713
00:24:19,820 --> 00:24:21,060
We should let players

714
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:22,300
focus on enjoying the game.

715
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:24,470
Everything goes back to the game itself.

716
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,260
I've modified it.

717
00:24:30,580 --> 00:24:32,630
(Are people still playing
the Divine Mountains and Seas?)

718
00:24:32,630 --> 00:24:34,230
(Seems like they quietly updated it.)

719
00:24:34,230 --> 00:24:36,820
(How smooth. Tengda actually listened.)

720
00:24:37,230 --> 00:24:39,260
(All the parts
we complained about are fixed.)

721
00:24:39,346 --> 00:24:41,435
(I ordered takeout in
the Divine Mountains and Seas.)

722
00:24:41,457 --> 00:24:44,540
(Half an hour later,
it actually arrived.)

723
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:46,710
(Tengda. Amazing.)

724
00:24:47,230 --> 00:24:48,780
(Tengda, what god-tier move is this?)

725
00:24:48,910 --> 00:24:50,500
(You can read web novels in-game?)

726
00:24:50,870 --> 00:24:53,870
(Zhongdian Web Fiction's novels
are a bit abstracted,)

727
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:56,870
(but the process of collecting
fragments is interesting.)

728
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:59,319
(The real-world collab in
the Divine Mountains and Seas)

729
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,613
(is incredible.)

730
00:25:00,820 --> 00:25:01,910
ID.

731
00:25:02,710 --> 00:25:04,150
Can't Compare to Boran.

732
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:06,390
The Divine Mountains and Seas, Zone 49,

733
00:25:06,390 --> 00:25:08,500
Revelers' Zone. Takeout has arrived.

734
00:25:08,630 --> 00:25:09,300
Whose is it?

735
00:25:10,340 --> 00:25:11,260
Mine.

736
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:13,020
Coming.

737
00:25:16,940 --> 00:25:18,540
(The Divine Mountains and Seas)

738
00:25:20,470 --> 00:25:21,060
It's out.

739
00:25:21,060 --> 00:25:22,060
The fragment dropped.

740
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:24,390
(The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You)
You got a fragment to read

741
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:25,580
the extra chapter
of Chit & Chat's novel.

742
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:27,340
I've always wanted
to read this extra chapter.

743
00:25:27,346 --> 00:25:28,902
But in The Divine Mountains and Seas,

744
00:25:28,902 --> 00:25:30,020
fragments drop randomly.

745
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:32,190
Each player gets different texts.

746
00:25:32,257 --> 00:25:34,235
Which dungeon
did you get this fragment from?

747
00:25:34,540 --> 00:25:36,540
(The Divine Mountains and Seas
launched a wishing mode,)

748
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:37,870
(collaborating
with Dreams Fulfilled Immediately.)

749
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,870
(Attention.
Dreams Fulfilled Immediately)

750
00:25:39,870 --> 00:25:40,910
(no longer receive private messages.)

751
00:25:40,910 --> 00:25:42,710
(Use the wishing pool
in the Divine Mountains and Seas.)

752
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:43,630
(I tested it, and it works.)

753
00:25:43,660 --> 00:25:44,710
(The Divine Mountains and Seas)

754
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:46,391
Travelers
of the Divine Mountains and Seas.

755
00:25:46,391 --> 00:25:47,020
Don't worry.

756
00:25:47,020 --> 00:25:47,740
So far,

757
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:50,060
we've received
tens of thousands of wishes

758
00:25:50,060 --> 00:25:51,230
from travelers.

759
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,780
(Please give us a little more time.)

760
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:53,740
(We'll help everyone...)

761
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:55,150
(We'll help... We...)

762
00:25:55,613 --> 00:25:57,702
(We'll help everyone
fulfill their wishes one by one.)

763
00:25:57,746 --> 00:25:58,950
(Stay tuned)

764
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:00,430
(to the Divine Mountains and Seas.)

765
00:26:00,430 --> 00:26:02,780
(Scan the QR code to download.)

766
00:26:05,870 --> 00:26:06,540
Ms. Tang.

767
00:26:06,591 --> 00:26:07,768
This player wants a free meal

768
00:26:07,768 --> 00:26:09,260
from the private kitchen. Approve?

769
00:26:09,260 --> 00:26:10,060
No problem, approved.

770
00:26:10,060 --> 00:26:11,060
Ms. Tang.

771
00:26:11,260 --> 00:26:12,990
This player wants to join Tengda.

772
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:13,829
How should we reply?

773
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:15,020
Thank them for their interest.

774
00:26:15,035 --> 00:26:15,910
And tell them to follow

775
00:26:15,910 --> 00:26:17,260
the recruitment info online.

776
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:18,060
Oh, right.

777
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:19,924
Give them
a few more sets of game equipment.

778
00:26:19,924 --> 00:26:20,546
Got it.

779
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:21,540
Ms. Tang.

780
00:26:21,540 --> 00:26:23,540
This player wants Lu Zhiyao's autograph.

781
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:28,500
Mr. Lu, I'm here to visit.

782
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:30,150
I need your help with something.

783
00:26:38,780 --> 00:26:39,580
Mr. Lu.

784
00:26:39,780 --> 00:26:40,340
Well...

785
00:26:40,340 --> 00:26:42,500
Could you provide
some autographed photos

786
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,346
for the Divine Mountains and Seas
players?

787
00:26:49,060 --> 00:26:49,990
Originally,

788
00:26:49,990 --> 00:26:51,990
I added a few lines to your character.

789
00:26:52,102 --> 00:26:55,470
But after thinking it through, it's
better to add them to Shi Huo instead.

790
00:27:00,302 --> 00:27:02,724
You add a few lines of dialogue,
and I'll sign a few autographs.

791
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:06,630
(Tang_Student)
(I really got Lu Zhiyao's autograph!)

792
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:07,946
(- I want one too.
- Me too!)

793
00:27:11,910 --> 00:27:13,710
Is that how you film vertical videos?

794
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:15,780
You just rotate the monitor vertically.

795
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:18,230
Where's everyone?

796
00:27:19,020 --> 00:27:19,740
Where's everyone?

797
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:21,780
Mr. Shi.

798
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:23,302
No, what's the rush in calling me over?

799
00:27:23,324 --> 00:27:24,430
I can't amend the script.

800
00:27:24,430 --> 00:27:26,340
Why should Lu Zhiyao's autograph

801
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:27,260
be used as a gift?

802
00:27:28,740 --> 00:27:30,340
It's Mr. Lu.

803
00:27:30,340 --> 00:27:31,780
He offered it voluntarily.

804
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:33,470
I'm not voluntary?

805
00:27:33,820 --> 00:27:34,950
I'll also provide some.

806
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:39,340
Enough.

807
00:27:39,470 --> 00:27:40,870
Enough.

808
00:27:41,260 --> 00:27:42,300
I believe many friends

809
00:27:42,300 --> 00:27:43,260
already received...

810
00:27:43,260 --> 00:27:45,740
(autographs from Shi Huo and Lu Zhiyao.)

811
00:27:46,020 --> 00:27:47,870
This collab in
the Divine Mountains and Seas

812
00:27:48,020 --> 00:27:50,190
breaks the barrier between
reality and the game world.

813
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:51,580
(Do you still have extra autographs?)
(Completely)

814
00:27:51,580 --> 00:27:53,260
(Can Mr. Qiao draw me too?)
(connecting them.)

815
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:55,260
(Truly an industry miracle.)

816
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:00,710
Okay, no problem.

817
00:28:00,710 --> 00:28:01,100
Mr. Zhou.

818
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:02,300
Mr. Zhou.

819
00:28:04,035 --> 00:28:04,990
Continue optimizing.

820
00:28:06,740 --> 00:28:07,260
What's up?

821
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:08,950
Tengda released a new update,

822
00:28:09,300 --> 00:28:11,100
fixing several
previously criticized points

823
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:12,100
and also implemented

824
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:13,409
an internal collab between the game

825
00:28:13,410 --> 00:28:15,020
and Tengda's ecosystem
to attract players.

826
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:15,780
Looks like

827
00:28:15,780 --> 00:28:16,580
it's working.

828
00:28:22,060 --> 00:28:23,910
Then find a way to suppress it.

829
00:28:24,470 --> 00:28:25,820
But the budget...

830
00:28:27,060 --> 00:28:28,020
Eric

831
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:29,060
might not give us

832
00:28:29,060 --> 00:28:30,190
that much support.

833
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:31,500
After all,

834
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:32,470
Fingle

835
00:28:32,470 --> 00:28:33,710
isn't ours either.

836
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:43,390
Just ignore it.

837
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:45,060
Keep going.

838
00:28:45,910 --> 00:28:47,150
As for Eric,

839
00:28:47,470 --> 00:28:48,390
I'll convince him.

840
00:28:57,820 --> 00:28:58,710
Come in.

841
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:06,740
Yada.

842
00:29:07,060 --> 00:29:08,020
Want something to eat?

843
00:29:08,020 --> 00:29:09,060
I'll order some takeout.

